text: Nay Toe ( ; born Nay Lin Aung on 9 September 1981) is a Rakhine ethnic Burmese film actor and comedian with the Burmese traditional dance troupe Htawara Hninzi. He won Myanmar Motion Picture Academy Awards for Best Actor three times: in 2009 with Moe Nya Einmet Myu, in 2015 with Nat Khat Mhar Tae Tite Pwal, in 2017 with Tar Tay Gyi, and in 2024 with Hnaung. He also won the Star Award for the film Bridge of Clouds in 2018. He is one of the highest-paid actors in Myanmar. Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Burmese actors
